    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in aerial RX data indication unpacking\n\n### Summary\nThe aerial VNF P7 message handler allocated memory for RX data indication PDUs but failed to free it on error paths. This caused a steady memory leak during operation when RX data indication messages contained invalid data or when memory allocation failed.\n\nThe fix adds proper error handling with cleanup for all allocation and unpacking failure paths.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/fapi_vnf_p7.c`: \n  - Added NULL checks after memory allocations in `aerial_unpack_nr_rx_data_indication_body`\n  - Added cleanup code in `aerial_unpack_nr_rx_data_indication` to free allocated PDUs and PDU list on all error paths\n  - Used proper `nfapi_p7_deallocate` function matching `nfapi_p7_allocate`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Run OAI gNB with AERIAL mode enabled\n2. Send malformed RX data indication messages from the PHY\n3. Monitor memory usage with `valgrind` or `pmap` - memory consumption will steadily increase\n4. Eventually system will run out of memory\n\nThe leak occurs because when unpacking fails partway through a message, previously allocated PDU buffers are not freed.\n"
}